# Cluster Architecture & kubeadm

You've **used** the control plane. Now open it up — the densest chapter, tested heavily.

```
Control plane                  Worker nodes
etcd ←→ apiserver ← kubectl    kubelet ─CRI→ runtime → Pods
         ↑ watch               kube-proxy · CNI
scheduler  controller-manager
```

## Four rules

- **Only the api-server touches etcd.** Everything else → api-server.
- **api-server is stateless** — scalable; state in etcd.
- **Controllers watch, don't poll** — a long-lived stream.
- **Nodes don't trust each other** — all authenticate to the api-server.

## The module

> etcd · api-server · scheduler+controllers · node components · CRI/CNI/CSI · static pods · kubeadm · PKI · **etcd backup** · upgrades.

> **The Control Plane + Node runtime boxes** — the Cluster column everything rides on.
